# .portforwarding — ports to expose from the Claude container (macOS only)
#
# On macOS, Docker's --network host connects to the Linux VM, not the Mac,
# so ports must be published explicitly. List them here, one per line.
#
# On Linux, the container uses host networking by default and this file
# is ignored (all ports are already accessible).
#
# Format:
#   <port>              — publish container port to the same host port
#   <from>-<to>         — publish a range of ports (e.g. 8001-8006)
#   <host>:<container>  — publish container port to a different host port
#
# Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines are ignored.
#
# Tip: dev servers inside the container must bind to 0.0.0.0, not 127.0.0.1,
# for port forwarding to work. Most frameworks: --host 0.0.0.0
#
# Tip: add "127.0.0.1 claudeboxed" to /etc/hosts on your Mac, then access
# services at http://claudeboxed:<port>

3000
8080
